cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SP 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of the outage probability of a dual-branch selection combiner in correlated Nakagami-m fading. This falls under the purview of information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the level crossing rate and average fade duration of a sampled Nakagami-m fading envelope. This is related to the control of systems and hence, could be categorized under cs.SI. 
3. cs.MS (Mathematical Software) - The paper derives closed-form expressions for the bivariate Nakagami-m cumulative distribution function in terms of hypergeometric functions. This could be of interest to researchers working on mathematical software. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper deals with the calculation of the level crossing rate and average fade duration of a sampled Nakagami-m fading envelope. This involves numerical analysis techniques. 
5. cs.SP (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with the analysis of the outage probability of a dual-branch selection combiner in correlated Nakagami-m fading. This is related to signal processing.
